<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127636>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Alitropus typus H. Milne Edwards 1840 (as Aega (Conilera) interrupta Von Martens, 1868), holotype female (15.0 mm; ZMB No. 3366). (a) Dorsal view; (b) ventral view; (c) lateral view; (d) ventral view of cephalon with mouthparts; (e) dorsal view of posterior region. Please replace in colour figures" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6127636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127638>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Alitropus typus H. Milne Edwards 1840 (as Aega (Conilera) interrupta Von Martens, 1868), holotype female (15.0 mm; ZMB No. 3366). (a) Dorsal view; (b) lateral view; (c) clypeal region." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6127638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127626>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Alitropus typus H. Milne Edwards 1840, male (19.0 mm; ZSI/MBRC D1-568). (a) Dorsal view; (b) antennula; (c) antenna; (d) mandible; (e) maxilla; (f) maxilliped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6127626/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127632>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Alitropus typus H. Milne Edwards 1840, male (19.0 mm; ZSI/MBRC D1-568). (a–e) Pereopods 1–4, 7, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6127632/files/figure.png" ;
